22:22.200 --> 22:24.077
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font></b>

22:30.920 --> 22:32.035
Lucas!

22:37.760 --> 22:38.829
<b><font color="#D900D9">(BANGING ON DOOR)</font></b>

22:39.040 --> 22:40.109
Alton!

22:50.920 --> 22:51.920
Stop!

22:52.800 --> 22:53.869
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON SCREAMING)</font></b>

22:54.040 --> 22:55.109
No!

22:55.280 --> 22:56.793
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SHUSHING)</font></b>

22:56.960 --> 22:57.960
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON GROANING)</font></b>

23:02.040 --> 23:03.109
No!

23:09.560 --> 23:12.472
I got you. I got you. I got you.

23:12.800 --> 23:14.711
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING SLOWS)</font></b>
- It's okay. It's okay.

23:14.880 --> 23:16.199
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SHUSHING)</font></b>

23:23.120 --> 23:24.553
<b><font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING STOPS)</font></b>

23:25.160 --> 23:26.309
<b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> <i>It's okay.</i>

23:27.120 --> 23:28.120
<i>It's okay.</i>

23:28.400 --> 23:29.628
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON CRYING)</font></b>

23:37.320 --> 23:39.117
<b><font color="#808080">HANNAH:</font></b>
Things would break.

23:41.240 --> 23:42.832
What kinds of things?

23:44.960 --> 23:47.838
Windows, light bulbs.

23:49.160 --> 23:51.720
Cars would shut down.
That kind of thing.

23:55.400 --> 23:57.789
It just got worse the older he got,

23:59.480 --> 24:01.311
so they just started letting
him sleep in the daytime,

24:01.480 --> 24:03.311
and he'd be awake at night.

24:04.320 --> 24:06.880
It's why all our services
are at night now.

24:07.480 --> 24:08.993
And what's your job
on the Ranch?

24:09.160 --> 24:10.354
<i>Childcare.</i>

24:11.840 --> 24:14.718
I help look after all
of Brother Calvin's children.

24:17.880 --> 24:21.190
Alton's been with him
over two years now.

24:22.240 --> 24:23.832
And the birth mother?

24:25.600 --> 24:27.238
She abandoned him.

24:28.520 --> 24:29.748
<b><font color="#808080">FREDRICK:</font></b>
<i>Yes, I'm done.</i>

24:29.920 --> 24:31.273
<b><font color="#808080">SEVIER:</font></b> Communing?

24:31.440 --> 24:33.112
That's what we call it.

24:34.480 --> 24:35.959
To be clear,

24:39.880 --> 24:42.713
"A visible spectrum of light
came from his eyes."

24:44.280 --> 24:45.429
Yes.

24:47.240 --> 24:49.231
And others have described seeing things.

24:49.400 --> 24:51.595
Did he show you things
during this process?

24:52.600 --> 24:53.749
Yes.

24:56.040 --> 24:58.156
<i>What kinds of things?</i>

24:59.080 --> 25:00.957
I wouldn't know where to start.

25:04.120 --> 25:06.839
And Friday, March 6th.
Why is this date important?

25:08.440 --> 25:10.351
It's the day of our judgment.

25:11.560 --> 25:13.232
What makes you say that?

25:14.880 --> 25:16.598
I believe it.

25:19.240 --> 25:21.435
<b><font color="#808080">CAROLINE:</font></b>
<i>It wasn't images.</i>

25:22.200 --> 25:23.918
Not what I remember.

25:24.840 --> 25:26.592
It was more...

25:28.440 --> 25:30.431
It was like a feeling.

25:31.080 --> 25:34.595
What kind of feeling?

25:39.120 --> 25:40.269
Comfort.

25:44.800 --> 25:46.472
And...

25:48.520 --> 25:51.114
what do you think will happen
on Friday, March 6th?

25:55.640 --> 26:00.191
If Alton is with us,
we will be saved.

26:02.960 --> 26:04.439
<b><font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)</font></b>

26:08.680 --> 26:10.432
<b><font color="#808080">FEMALE AGENT:</font></b>
<i>Barbara Meyer?</i>

26:15.240 --> 26:16.639
This way.

26:17.520 --> 26:19.750
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font></b> All right. I need
everyone to stand up.

26:19.920 --> 26:21.672
Exit through the front doors, please.

26:26.120 --> 26:27.917
Single file, please. Thank you.

26:44.360 --> 26:46.032
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING IN RELIEF)</font></b>

27:51.880 --> 27:54.155
<b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> Lucas,
can you get Alton in the van?

27:54.880 --> 27:55.880
Yeah.

28:08.400 --> 28:10.118
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(INHALES DEEPLY)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(DOOR CLOSES)</font></b>

28:28.120 --> 28:29.314
We're taking your van.

28:37.680 --> 28:39.113
Please don't.

28:39.760 --> 28:41.751
You know where we're going.

28:43.320 --> 28:44.469
<i>Please.</i>

28:46.800 --> 28:49.758
I had to see again.

28:50.680 --> 28:52.750
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ELDEN BREATHING HEAVILY)</font></b>

28:55.120 --> 28:56.997
You knew better.

29:18.600 --> 29:20.192
<b><font color="#808080">FEMALE DISPATCHER:</font></b> <b><font color="#D900D9">(ON RADIO)</font></b>
<i>Liberty 285. Code 6.</i>

29:20.400 --> 29:22.277
<i>105 North Avenue, 52.</i>

29:25.360 --> 29:27.000
<b><font color="#D900D9">(FEMALE DISPATCHER
CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)</font></b>

29:34.720 --> 29:36.358
<b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> <i>We need to stop
for gas.</i>

29:37.040 --> 29:39.156
We could use some supplies.

29:40.240 --> 29:41.673
<i>I'll go in.</i>

29:43.040 --> 29:44.680
The less people that see you,
the better.

29:46.560 --> 29:48.676
I need to use the payphone.

29:52.600 --> 29:54.238
What's Kryptonite?

29:56.320 --> 29:58.629
It's the only thing
that'll kill Superman.

29:58.800 --> 30:00.358
<b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> <i>It's made-up.</i>

30:02.040 --> 30:03.553
I should have never let you
give him those.

30:03.720 --> 30:05.360
He's never seen
a comic book in his life.

30:05.960 --> 30:09.032
That's why he needs them.
Reading's reading.

30:10.440 --> 30:12.590
He needs to know
what's real.

30:20.240 --> 30:21.639
He looks weaker.

30:23.960 --> 30:25.109
He is.

30:26.480 --> 30:27.754
He recovers?

30:29.480 --> 30:30.708
He's fine.

30:41.760 --> 30:43.671
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING SPANISH)</font></b>

30:52.360 --> 30:53.713
He speaks Spanish?

30:55.080 --> 30:57.913
It's something he does.
Turn on the radio.

31:02.680 --> 31:04.159
Scroll through the stations.

31:06.160 --> 31:08.435
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON COPYING MAN ON RADIO
SPEAKING SPANISH)</font></b>

31:14.080 --> 31:16.116
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LATIN MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)</font></b>

31:32.560 --> 31:33.788
Be right back.

31:34.920 --> 31:35.955
Stay in the van.

31:38.720 --> 31:39.720
<b><font color="#D900D9">(VAN DOOR CLOSES)</font></b>

32:37.360 --> 32:38.429
Hey.

32:42.560 --> 32:45.518
Yeah, we're okay.
We should be there in a couple hours.

33:03.560 --> 33:04.959
<b><font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font></b> Are you okay?

33:06.920 --> 33:08.558
I've been wanting to see you.

33:10.800 --> 33:11.800
Mmm-hmm.

33:17.680 --> 33:18.999
We'll be there soon.

33:24.760 --> 33:26.751
Why are you wearing
those goggles?

33:26.920 --> 33:28.148
<b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> Stop! Stop!

33:29.800 --> 33:31.438
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ROY PANTING)</font></b>

33:32.440 --> 33:34.032
He's with me. He's my son.

33:35.680 --> 33:37.716
Yeah, well,
you ought to watch your kid.

33:37.880 --> 33:39.598
Yeah, I got it. Thank you.

33:41.000 --> 33:42.433
Everything okay?

33:46.760 --> 33:50.309
You cannot leave the van.
You hear me?

33:52.040 --> 33:53.109
I'm sorry.

34:01.320 --> 34:03.436
It's okay.
I shouldn't have left you.

34:06.080 --> 34:07.308
No.

34:10.040 --> 34:11.234
I'm sorry.

34:25.159 --> 34:26.275
Roy?

34:40.840 --> 34:41.840
<b><font color="#D900D9">(LUCAS YELPS)</font></b>

34:46.360 --> 34:47.360
- Go!
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

34:48.840 --> 34:49.989
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

35:10.080 --> 35:11.080
Dad?

35:13.680 --> 35:15.716
Alton. Lean your head back.

35:16.800 --> 35:18.438
- <b><font color="#808080">LUCAS:</font></b> Is he okay?
- Yeah.

35:19.000 --> 35:20.274
Roy.

35:20.440 --> 35:22.476
Roy, do we need to get him
to a hospital?

35:22.680 --> 35:24.272
No! No! Just keep driving.

35:24.600 --> 35:26.318
Is this something that he does?

35:27.200 --> 35:28.758
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

35:32.640 --> 35:33.755
It's okay.

35:35.160 --> 35:36.195
It's okay.

35:38.160 --> 35:39.434
<b><font color="#D900D9">(VEHICLE APPROACHING)</font></b>

36:12.560 --> 36:13.595
<b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> Alton.

36:16.920 --> 36:18.478
Thank you, God.

36:18.760 --> 36:19.760
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFLING)</font></b>

36:20.080 --> 36:21.433
Thank you.

36:24.360 --> 36:25.839
Let me look at you.

36:31.000 --> 36:32.274
You're so big.

36:34.440 --> 36:35.793
So grown-up.

36:42.000 --> 36:43.558
- Hello.
- Hi.

36:44.480 --> 36:45.674
I'm Sarah.

36:47.440 --> 36:48.589
Lucas.

37:02.480 --> 37:03.833
How are you?

37:06.960 --> 37:08.439
I missed him.

37:18.040 --> 37:19.189
Come on.
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font></b>

37:20.200 --> 37:21.838
Y'all must be exhausted.

37:22.520 --> 37:24.158
Let's go inside.

37:25.240 --> 37:27.071
I got a present for you, Alton.

37:32.240 --> 37:33.878
You wanna see your room?

37:45.800 --> 37:48.473
I can't keep my eyes off him.

38:19.920 --> 38:21.512
Get some rest.

38:23.840 --> 38:24.989
Okay.

38:37.640 --> 38:38.993
<b><font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS)</font></b>

38:49.480 --> 38:50.754
He okay?

38:53.440 --> 38:55.192
He doesn't look good.

38:55.800 --> 38:57.233
He's sick.

38:58.840 --> 39:01.070
He's getting weaker,
but he'll be okay.

39:02.400 --> 39:04.072
Should we do something?

39:04.600 --> 39:07.068
Just stick to the plan
and get him there by Friday.

39:07.280 --> 39:09.271
Do you think that's wise?

39:09.440 --> 39:10.759
It's all we have.

39:11.760 --> 39:14.115
This date and place is everything.

39:14.280 --> 39:16.111
We take him to a hospital,
it's over.

39:16.280 --> 39:17.918
But if it's between that
and him dying?

39:19.480 --> 39:22.074
It's three days.
He'll make it.

39:31.960 --> 39:33.518
I think he's right.

39:37.800 --> 39:38.994
Yeah.

39:41.040 --> 39:43.952
I don't know if there's a way
out of all this for y'all,

39:44.120 --> 39:45.917
but it's a shame.

39:47.240 --> 39:49.629
You would have made
a nice family otherwise.

39:55.640 --> 39:56.834
<b><font color="#D900D9">(DOOR CLOSES)</font></b>

40:08.440 --> 40:10.431
I'm an electrician.

40:12.240 --> 40:14.276
Certified in two states.

40:17.720 --> 40:20.109
What do I know about these things?

40:21.680 --> 40:22.829
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font></b>

40:23.240 --> 40:25.674
He wouldn't have asked you
if you couldn't do it.

40:32.080 --> 40:35.390
Sometimes we are asked to do things
that are beyond us.

40:51.280 --> 40:52.315
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNS COCKING)</font></b>

41:29.000 --> 41:30.000
Yes?

41:31.560 --> 41:33.551
Are you Sarah Tomlin's mother?

42:28.000 --> 42:31.470
How could someone
cause a satellite to fall out of orbit?

42:32.120 --> 42:33.633
I don't know. Ask an engineer.

42:35.680 --> 42:36.680
Well...

42:37.480 --> 42:40.472
Alton Meyer brought down
an Air Force satellite last night.

42:47.400 --> 42:49.311
DSP-9712.

42:51.520 --> 42:54.478
- It was tasked with detecting a...
- Nuclear explosion.

42:55.200 --> 42:56.200
Yeah.

42:57.160 --> 43:00.516
This is the last image
sent to us by the satellite.

43:00.720 --> 43:04.554
We believe that's the boy
standing at the center of the heat bloom.

43:04.720 --> 43:06.560
It's not exactly a heat bloom,
but that's fine.

43:06.680 --> 43:09.478
Well, whatever it is,
it set off a satellite

43:09.640 --> 43:12.837
whose sole purpose
is detecting a nuclear event.

43:29.480 --> 43:31.152
No radiation.

43:32.040 --> 43:33.155
None.

43:35.760 --> 43:37.478
Could a drone be programmed

43:37.640 --> 43:39.949
to search for that
specific heat signature?

43:40.880 --> 43:41.880
Yeah.

43:45.280 --> 43:49.114
We've got a field office in Mobile
you can base your team out of.

43:49.680 --> 43:51.800
- What about the interviews?
- You're done with those.

43:51.880 --> 43:55.395
Like it or not, you're
the new resident expert on Alton Meyer.

43:55.560 --> 43:56.993
Let's go.

44:02.360 --> 44:03.509
<b><font color="#808080">FEMALE NEWSCASTER:</font></b>
<i>Breaking news at this hour.</i>

44:03.680 --> 44:07.832
<i>A weather satellite fell from space
and crashed near a gas station.</i>

44:08.040 --> 44:10.554
<i>This happened overnight
in northern Louisiana,</i>

44:10.720 --> 44:13.837
<i>and as we speak,
a massive cleanup is underway</i>

44:14.040 --> 44:18.352
<i>because the debris field from the crash
is nearly 60 miles wide.</i>

44:18.880 --> 44:20.996
<i>The Canadian company
that owns this satellite</i>

44:21.160 --> 44:23.310
<i>says the spacecraft
suffered mechanical failure...</i>

44:24.240 --> 44:26.913
Can you tell Lucas
to pull the van around back?

44:29.640 --> 44:31.471
Okay.

44:31.640 --> 44:35.519
<i>It is the first time that debris
has fallen in a populated area.</i>

44:35.680 --> 44:39.753
<i>Our local affiliate has more from the area
hardest hit by this falling debris.</i>

44:52.000 --> 44:54.560
Roy asked if you'd pull the van
around back when you're done.

44:56.320 --> 44:57.594
Okay.

44:59.600 --> 45:02.160
You're not from the Ranch?

45:02.920 --> 45:04.717
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b> No. No.

45:07.120 --> 45:08.951
<i>Then how do you know Roy?</i>

45:09.440 --> 45:10.793
We grew up together.

45:12.240 --> 45:14.595
We were real close
for a long time,

45:15.920 --> 45:19.993
till his parents moved him
out to the Ranch, and then we fell off.

45:22.480 --> 45:25.438
Until three nights ago,
there was a knock at my door,

45:25.600 --> 45:29.479
and there's Roy
standing there with Alton.

45:30.480 --> 45:32.755
He says that they're in trouble
and they need help.

45:35.760 --> 45:38.433
And then Alton sat me down.

45:39.600 --> 45:42.114
And he took those goggles off.

45:47.120 --> 45:49.680
You know when that boy does that...

45:53.160 --> 45:55.151
That thing with his eyes...

46:05.400 --> 46:06.833
It's powerful.

46:19.760 --> 46:21.910
What do you do in San Angelo?

46:24.920 --> 46:26.751
I'm a state trooper.

46:48.760 --> 46:50.034
<b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> <i>Alton?</i>

47:13.240 --> 47:14.309
Alton?

47:16.680 --> 47:17.829
Yes?

47:19.400 --> 47:21.595
What happened
at the gas station?

47:21.760 --> 47:23.591
<i>Did you mean to do that?</i>

47:25.560 --> 47:26.560
Yes.

47:29.080 --> 47:30.229
Why?

47:31.080 --> 47:32.308
They were watching me.

47:34.800 --> 47:36.916
Who was watching you, Alton?

47:40.320 --> 47:41.548
The police.

47:43.440 --> 47:45.351
Well, how do you know
it was the police?

47:46.240 --> 47:48.549
They talk like
the police on your radio.

47:52.120 --> 47:53.758
What do they say?

47:55.360 --> 47:57.112
They're looking for me.

48:20.200 --> 48:22.668
Here's a receipt for her car insurance.

48:22.840 --> 48:25.149
Isuzu Rodeo, '99.

48:26.080 --> 48:27.991
There's a van in the driveway.

48:30.160 --> 48:32.390
See if it's got a registration in it.

48:48.000 --> 48:49.353
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON COUGHING)</font></b>

48:51.480 --> 48:52.480
Alton.

48:53.800 --> 48:54.949
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font></b>

48:56.320 --> 48:58.834
Alton. Breathe. Can you breathe?

49:00.200 --> 49:01.599
- Roy!
- Pull over.

49:01.840 --> 49:03.637
- <b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> <i>Breathe!</i>
- Pull over!

49:08.760 --> 49:10.239
Breathe! Breathe!

49:12.200 --> 49:13.428
Breathe.

49:16.800 --> 49:17.800
<b><font color="#D900D9">(EXHALES)</font></b>

49:19.680 --> 49:21.511
Okay, okay.

49:36.440 --> 49:37.475
What is it?

49:42.400 --> 49:43.800
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GROANS)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(CAR ALARM BLARING)</font></b>

49:45.640 --> 49:46.640
Mom?

49:46.920 --> 49:47.920
I'm okay.

49:50.120 --> 49:51.120
Ahhh!

49:51.280 --> 49:52.315
Mom?

49:52.600 --> 49:54.033
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

49:59.080 --> 50:00.149
<b><font color="#808080">LUCAS:</font></b> God.

50:04.200 --> 50:05.200
Alton.

50:09.440 --> 50:10.555
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(RETCHES)</font></b>
- Alton!

50:12.800 --> 50:14.631
Water! He needs water.

50:18.760 --> 50:19.760
Oh, my God.

50:24.320 --> 50:25.320
<b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> <i>Alton.</i>

50:26.240 --> 50:27.275
Roy.

50:29.960 --> 50:31.439
<b><font color="#D900D9">(WHEEZING)</font></b>

50:33.120 --> 50:34.120
He needs water.

50:34.760 --> 50:36.352
We need to take him to a hospital!

50:36.840 --> 50:38.512
- No.
- He's dying.

50:39.600 --> 50:40.919
Hey, hey!

50:41.080 --> 50:42.877
- He is sick, right?
- No!

50:43.040 --> 50:45.793
- <b><font color="#808080">LUCAS:</font></b> <i>He's dying!</i>
- <b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> <i>No! He will not die!</i>

50:45.960 --> 50:47.518
He is meant for something else!

50:47.680 --> 50:49.079
No, he's sick and he needs help!

50:52.040 --> 50:53.040
Alton?

50:58.200 --> 51:01.033
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b> We have to go.
They're coming.

51:01.880 --> 51:03.313
Who's coming?

51:05.320 --> 51:06.320
There.

51:17.160 --> 51:18.878
You take the car with Lucas.

51:21.240 --> 51:23.071
Dad, we have to go.

51:24.520 --> 51:25.748
That way.

51:26.840 --> 51:27.909
Now!

51:31.240 --> 51:32.514
Roy... Roy!

51:42.440 --> 51:43.714
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font></b> What the hell?

51:51.920 --> 51:53.353
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ROY PANTING)</font></b>

51:56.360 --> 51:57.360
<b><font color="#D900D9">(YELPS)</font></b>

51:58.640 --> 52:01.029
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

52:01.880 --> 52:03.199
I can run.

52:03.800 --> 52:04.949
This way.

52:16.040 --> 52:17.075
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

52:42.120 --> 52:43.599
<b><font color="#D900D9">(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)</font></b>

53:01.120 --> 53:02.120
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

53:04.440 --> 53:05.440
Alton.

53:24.160 --> 53:25.400
How did you know this was here?

53:28.960 --> 53:30.109
I didn't.

53:37.120 --> 53:39.350
Sun will be up in a few hours.

53:40.720 --> 53:42.438
<i>We can wait out the daylight here.</i>

53:43.040 --> 53:44.040
<b><font color="#D900D9">(THUDDING)</font></b>

53:44.360 --> 53:45.554
Alton!

53:54.960 --> 53:55.960
Here.

54:07.680 --> 54:09.079
I'm okay.

54:13.840 --> 54:15.398
I'm sorry.

54:18.680 --> 54:19.874
No.

54:27.880 --> 54:29.677
<i>I need something.</i>

54:30.560 --> 54:31.675
What?

54:32.320 --> 54:34.993
I need to be awake during the day.

54:36.320 --> 54:37.320
In the sun.

54:41.200 --> 54:42.394
You can't.

54:48.560 --> 54:49.834
I have to.

54:51.800 --> 54:53.552
It could kill you.

54:58.320 --> 54:59.548
Dad...

55:05.600 --> 55:07.238
I have to.

56:01.760 --> 56:03.751
He's not going to Atlanta.

56:08.480 --> 56:09.595
What?

56:12.920 --> 56:15.673
All these places mentioned in the sermons,
they don't matter.

56:15.840 --> 56:17.910
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font></b> They don't?

56:19.120 --> 56:22.112
No, he's just listening
to the government talk.

56:25.080 --> 56:27.071
He's just looking
for a language to describe a location,

56:27.240 --> 56:29.071
and all he heard was coordinates.

56:57.040 --> 56:58.678
That's remarkable.

57:08.240 --> 57:10.834
Now they wanna move us
to an office in Atlanta.

57:11.000 --> 57:12.638
Doesn't matter.

57:12.800 --> 57:13.800
What?

57:13.960 --> 57:15.757
I know where they're going.

57:31.320 --> 57:32.469
Old habits die hard?

57:36.880 --> 57:38.871
You still staying up nights?

57:44.680 --> 57:46.875
What happened to your head, Elden?

57:51.880 --> 57:53.074
<b><font color="#808080">MALE NEWSCASTER:</font></b> <b><font color="#D900D9">(ON TV)</font></b>
<i>...then warming up a bit</i>

57:53.320 --> 57:54.719
<i>this afternoon, with a few sunny breaks</i>

57:54.880 --> 57:56.029
<i>and diminishing...</i>

57:56.480 --> 57:58.240
<b><font color="#808080">MALE ANNOUNCER:</font></b>
<i>So you can go one full year...</i>

57:58.280 --> 58:00.200
<i>This is the part that people
need to be aware of.</i>

58:00.240 --> 58:01.640
<i>- Everybody out...</i>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(TURNS OFF TV)</font></b>

58:03.520 --> 58:04.873
Roy will get him here.

58:05.400 --> 58:07.197
If he's not dead.

58:13.920 --> 58:15.114
I'm sorry.

58:16.520 --> 58:18.317
Roy won't let that happen.

58:19.640 --> 58:21.358
Yeah, I hope not.

58:23.560 --> 58:26.597
He believes in something.
You don't.

58:27.440 --> 58:28.919
<i>It doesn't matter.</i>

58:30.240 --> 58:33.073
Good people die every day
believing in things.

58:37.920 --> 58:42.072
Roy spent two years
watching another man raise our son.

58:47.320 --> 58:49.072
He did what I couldn't.

58:53.440 --> 58:55.670
He'll do anything to get him here.

59:02.480 --> 59:04.436
Better get some rest.

59:07.120 --> 59:09.475
Nobody's coming with the sun up.

01:00:36.760 --> 01:00:37.875
Dad.

01:00:40.880 --> 01:00:42.279
It's okay.

01:01:16.640 --> 01:01:17.755
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON GROANS SOFTLY)</font></b>

01:01:19.240 --> 01:01:21.390
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(SHUSHING)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON BREATHING HEAVILY)</font></b>

01:01:22.520 --> 01:01:23.748
<b><font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING)</font></b>

01:01:30.600 --> 01:01:31.828
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ALTON GROANING)</font></b>

01:01:45.760 --> 01:01:46.795
<b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> Dad.

01:02:08.480 --> 01:02:09.515
<b><font color="#D900D9">(KNOCK ON DOOR)</font></b>

01:02:18.800 --> 01:02:20.518
It's still daylight.

01:02:32.600 --> 01:02:33.794
Jesus.

01:02:44.800 --> 01:02:46.153
He looks...

01:02:48.440 --> 01:02:50.192
He has something to tell you.

01:03:00.120 --> 01:03:01.951
You look wonderful.

01:03:05.640 --> 01:03:07.119
It's still daylight.

01:03:07.920 --> 01:03:09.035
Yeah.

01:03:10.320 --> 01:03:12.038
No... No goggles.

01:03:32.800 --> 01:03:35.633
Lucas, you wanna sit down?

01:03:48.160 --> 01:03:49.479
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font></b>

01:03:52.760 --> 01:03:54.910
I saw the sunrise this morning.

01:03:56.480 --> 01:03:58.789
I think I know what I am now.

01:04:08.280 --> 01:04:09.554
There's...

01:04:10.080 --> 01:04:11.593
There's a world

01:04:12.480 --> 01:04:14.550
built on top of ours.

01:04:16.160 --> 01:04:17.957
People live there.

01:04:39.280 --> 01:04:41.475
I think they're like me.

01:05:10.640 --> 01:05:12.153
We saw it.

01:05:25.080 --> 01:05:26.957
They're like you?

01:05:29.520 --> 01:05:31.272
Yes, I think so.

01:05:36.680 --> 01:05:38.272
I understand.

01:05:55.160 --> 01:05:56.354
Lucas?

01:06:00.720 --> 01:06:02.199
I believe you.

01:06:05.560 --> 01:06:06.709
Good.

01:06:08.560 --> 01:06:09.709
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font></b>

01:06:11.560 --> 01:06:12.959
All right.

01:06:27.200 --> 01:06:28.349
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SHOWER RUNNING)</font></b>

01:06:32.400 --> 01:06:34.550
- You all right in there?
- <b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> <i>Yeah.</i>

01:06:44.760 --> 01:06:45.988
Roy?

01:06:46.960 --> 01:06:48.757
I need to talk to you.

01:06:50.560 --> 01:06:51.560
Okay.

01:06:56.760 --> 01:06:58.079
It's about tomorrow.

01:07:03.160 --> 01:07:04.832
The world you saw,

01:07:05.840 --> 01:07:07.751
it didn't last very long.

01:07:11.040 --> 01:07:12.439
Seconds.

01:07:13.960 --> 01:07:15.916
<b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b>
<i>And then he got better.</i>

01:07:18.040 --> 01:07:19.234
Yeah.

01:07:20.480 --> 01:07:22.277
What are you asking?

01:07:25.280 --> 01:07:28.033
What if Alton doesn't belong with us?

01:07:32.560 --> 01:07:34.630
<i>We need to consider that,</i>

01:07:36.960 --> 01:07:38.598
come tomorrow,

01:07:40.360 --> 01:07:41.998
he may be gone.

01:07:44.440 --> 01:07:45.589
<b><font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS)</font></b>

01:07:46.520 --> 01:07:48.033
<b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> <i>I'm out.</i>

01:07:54.480 --> 01:07:56.869
So you had never seen the sunrise?

01:07:57.240 --> 01:07:58.275
No.

01:07:58.480 --> 01:07:59.595
<i>Did you like it?</i>

01:08:01.520 --> 01:08:03.158
<i>What color was it?</i>

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:07.788
<b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> <i>It was first red,
then it was orange.</i>

01:08:12.120 --> 01:08:13.120
Okay.

01:08:17.960 --> 01:08:20.679
So, then you just walked out...

01:08:20.960 --> 01:08:22.040
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(SARAH SCREAMS)</font></b>

01:08:22.240 --> 01:08:23.309
<b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> <i>Alton! Alton!</i>

01:08:28.200 --> 01:08:29.200
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:08:29.399 --> 01:08:30.832
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CHOKING)</font></b>

01:08:31.600 --> 01:08:32.600
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GUNSHOT)</font></b>

01:08:36.760 --> 01:08:38.398
- <b><font color="#808080">LEVI:</font></b> Get down!
- No, no.

01:08:38.560 --> 01:08:39.629
<b><font color="#808080">LEVI:</font></b> That's enough.
Don't you move.

01:08:39.840 --> 01:08:41.068
- Stay down.
- <b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> No!

01:08:41.479 --> 01:08:43.515
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:08:47.560 --> 01:08:48.754
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font></b>

01:08:56.560 --> 01:08:57.560
No!

01:08:59.120 --> 01:09:00.348
<i>No!</i>

01:09:09.399 --> 01:09:10.594
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SARAH SCREAMING)</font></b>

01:09:12.520 --> 01:09:13.714
<b><font color="#D900D9">(STRAINING)</font></b>

01:09:17.600 --> 01:09:19.238
<b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> <i>No! No!</i>

01:09:19.880 --> 01:09:21.631
No! No, no!

01:09:21.840 --> 01:09:23.158
- <b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> Alton!
- No!

01:09:23.319 --> 01:09:24.319
Mom!

01:09:25.760 --> 01:09:26.760
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font></b>

01:09:26.920 --> 01:09:28.148
Mom!

01:09:28.439 --> 01:09:29.439
Alton!

01:09:31.240 --> 01:09:32.240
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font></b>

01:09:33.920 --> 01:09:34.955
No. <b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font></b>

01:09:38.520 --> 01:09:40.192
- <b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> Dad!
- No!

01:09:40.800 --> 01:09:42.916
<i>No! No!</i>

01:09:43.120 --> 01:09:44.394
<b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> No!

01:09:44.560 --> 01:09:45.629
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING)</font></b>

01:09:46.080 --> 01:09:48.229
Doak, don't. Please.

01:09:53.439 --> 01:09:54.509
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

01:09:56.040 --> 01:09:57.109
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font></b>

01:09:59.440 --> 01:10:00.634
- <b><font color="#808080">LUCAS:</font></b> <i>Roy!</i>
- No!

01:10:00.840 --> 01:10:02.512
<b><font color="#808080">ROY:</font></b> <i>Stop! Stop!</i>

01:10:05.920 --> 01:10:07.035
<i>- Stop!</i>
- <b><font color="#808080">LUCAS:</font></b> <i>Hey.</i>

01:10:07.200 --> 01:10:09.191
My boot. In my boot.

01:10:11.120 --> 01:10:13.031
Get me out! Get me out!

01:10:19.640 --> 01:10:20.675
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TYRES SCREECHING)</font></b>

01:10:26.080 --> 01:10:27.080
<b><font color="#808080">LUCAS:</font></b> Go!

01:10:41.560 --> 01:10:43.198
Man, I'm sorry, Roy.

01:10:43.840 --> 01:10:45.478
I just didn't see them coming.

01:11:17.520 --> 01:11:18.520
Back on the road, guys.

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:24.672
Hey, asshole!

01:11:24.880 --> 01:11:26.598
<i>Back on the road now!</i>

01:11:27.200 --> 01:11:28.349
Roy!

01:11:56.320 --> 01:11:57.514
<b><font color="#D900D9">(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)</font></b>

01:13:12.560 --> 01:13:13.560
<b><font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font></b>

01:13:33.760 --> 01:13:35.113
<b><font color="#808080">LUCAS:</font></b> FBI,

01:13:36.080 --> 01:13:39.231
<i>CIA, Homeland Security...</i>

01:13:39.480 --> 01:13:42.517
Someone has him.
Someone knows where he is.

01:13:44.360 --> 01:13:45.998
And the FBI have field offices.

01:13:46.160 --> 01:13:47.800
<b><font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERING)</font></b>
Now, we could start there...

01:13:47.920 --> 01:13:49.638
We won't find him.

01:13:58.280 --> 01:13:59.793
He's gone.

01:14:14.840 --> 01:14:17.957
The only thing I ever
believed in was Alton.

01:14:21.880 --> 01:14:23.518
And I failed him.

01:15:15.560 --> 01:15:16.560
<b><font color="#D900D9">(DOOR CLOSES)</font></b>

01:15:21.640 --> 01:15:23.756
Hello, Alton.
My name is Sharon Davison.

01:15:23.920 --> 01:15:25.911
I'm a childhood development counselor.

01:15:26.320 --> 01:15:28.754
<i>I consult with
the Federal Bureau of Investigation,</i>

01:15:28.960 --> 01:15:30.837
<i>but I'm not in law enforcement.</i>

01:15:32.960 --> 01:15:35.474
<i>I need to ask you some questions, okay?</i>

01:15:37.640 --> 01:15:40.313
<i>There was a crash
at a gas station you were at.</i>

01:15:40.480 --> 01:15:41.833
<i>Do you remember that?</i>

01:15:47.960 --> 01:15:49.791
Who has been with you the last few days?

01:15:54.120 --> 01:15:55.917
Have you been with your father?

01:15:56.120 --> 01:15:57.792
<b><font color="#D900D9">(INAUDIBLE)</font></b>

01:16:03.320 --> 01:16:05.151
I'm sorry, I didn't hear that.

01:16:07.280 --> 01:16:08.679
<i>Paul.</i>

01:16:10.200 --> 01:16:11.553
Who is that?

01:16:12.920 --> 01:16:15.229
<i>I want to talk to Paul Sevier.</i>

01:16:29.520 --> 01:16:31.670
- My name is...
- <b><font color="#808080">ALTON:</font></b> Paul Sevier.

01:16:32.280 --> 01:16:34.555
<i>Lead Operations Analyst.</i>

01:16:37.520 --> 01:16:39.795
They just gave me that title.

01:16:55.560 --> 01:16:56.913
Who is this guy?

01:16:57.600 --> 01:16:59.192
He's NSA.

01:17:17.200 --> 01:17:18.474
<i>What, uh...</i>

01:17:21.720 --> 01:17:23.392
The place that you and your father
were trying to get to,

01:17:23.560 --> 01:17:24.879
what's the significance of that location?

01:17:25.040 --> 01:17:26.951
<i>I will only speak with him.</i>

01:17:33.440 --> 01:17:34.839
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TURNS OFF INTERCOM)</font></b>

01:17:39.080 --> 01:17:40.877
Okay, everybody out.

01:17:51.560 --> 01:17:53.073
Just get the information.

01:18:03.280 --> 01:18:04.474
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TURNS ON INTERCOM)</font></b>

01:18:07.080 --> 01:18:09.196
Okay, so where do we start?

01:18:36.960 --> 01:18:38.951
That's impressive.

01:18:40.480 --> 01:18:41.993
<b><font color="#D900D9">(DOOR LOCK BEEPING)</font></b>

01:18:42.720 --> 01:18:43.835
<b><font color="#D900D9">(DOOR UNLOCKS)</font></b>

01:19:41.920 --> 01:19:43.239
You know, I have to say,

01:19:43.400 --> 01:19:45.834
I've really been looking forward
to meeting you.

01:19:55.920 --> 01:19:57.876
They think you're a weapon.

01:20:00.640 --> 01:20:01.993
I'm not.

01:20:02.920 --> 01:20:05.229
And the Ranch thinks you're their savior.

01:20:06.560 --> 01:20:08.551
<i>I'm not any of those things.</i>

01:20:11.960 --> 01:20:14.235
I belong in another world.

01:20:16.880 --> 01:20:18.711
<i>There are people there.</i>

01:20:20.960 --> 01:20:22.791
<i>They watch us.</i>

01:20:25.560 --> 01:20:28.677
They've been watching us
for a very long time.

01:20:29.680 --> 01:20:30.908
<b><font color="#D900D9">(GASPS SOFTLY)</font></b>

01:20:36.560 --> 01:20:38.755
I need to go where I belong.

01:20:44.520 --> 01:20:46.272
Where you belong?

01:21:22.560 --> 01:21:23.879
<b><font color="#D900D9">(TELEPHONE RINGING)</font></b>

01:21:43.520 --> 01:21:45.192
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PAYPHONES RINGING)</font></b>

01:21:47.720 --> 01:21:49.073
<b><font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font></b>

01:21:49.840 --> 01:21:50.840
Hello?

01:21:51.000 --> 01:21:53.468
- <b><font color="#808080">SEVIER:</font></b> <i>Is this Roy Tomlin?</i>
- Yes.

01:21:56.240 --> 01:21:58.037
<i>I have your son.</i>

01:22:03.160 --> 01:22:04.760
Yes, he's fine.
I'm bringing him to you.

01:22:05.840 --> 01:22:07.751
Do you have something
to write with?

01:22:10.160 --> 01:22:11.195
Okay.

01:22:15.240 --> 01:22:16.240
<b><font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font></b> Alton!

01:22:17.840 --> 01:22:19.319
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CAR LOCK BEEPS)</font></b>

01:22:28.320 --> 01:22:29.514
Ready?

01:22:32.680 --> 01:22:36.878
29 degrees, 4 minutes,
31 seconds north,

01:22:37.880 --> 01:22:43.079
82 degrees, 41 minutes,
48 seconds west.

01:22:43.240 --> 01:22:44.920
I'll have him there in four hours.
Goodbye.

01:22:57.600 --> 01:22:58.600
<b><font color="#D900D9">(CAR DOOR OPENS)</font></b>

01:23:06.960 --> 01:23:08.234
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE STARTING)</font></b>

01:23:33.080 --> 01:23:34.354
<b><font color="#808080">MILLER:</font></b> What about
the backup generator?

01:23:34.520 --> 01:23:37.240
<b><font color="#808080">BASE COMMANDER:</font></b> They've all failed.
I've never seen anything like it.

01:23:38.080 --> 01:23:39.274
And the exits?

01:23:39.440 --> 01:23:42.113
We have three.
The gates to each one were open.

01:23:42.280 --> 01:23:44.510
We can't get them closed without power.

01:24:01.440 --> 01:24:02.760
<b><font color="#808080">MILITARY OFFICER:</font></b>
Let's move out.

01:24:02.800 --> 01:24:05.633
<i>All right, moving out! Let's get
this place cleaned up right away!</i>

01:24:05.800 --> 01:24:06.800
Move! Move!

01:24:06.960 --> 01:24:08.678
You over there, take that side.

01:24:08.840 --> 01:24:10.637
Let's go. Move it, move it, move it!

01:24:58.720 --> 01:25:00.631
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

01:25:06.840 --> 01:25:07.955
<b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> Al.

01:25:16.240 --> 01:25:19.357
I decoded the same patterns
you found in the sermons.

01:25:19.520 --> 01:25:21.317
They know where you're going.

01:25:22.360 --> 01:25:24.999
Everything will be blocked off
for 5 miles.

01:25:26.200 --> 01:25:27.872
You won't get through.

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:34.433
I can help.

01:25:41.040 --> 01:25:42.439
<b><font color="#808080">SARAH:</font></b> Come on.

01:25:49.880 --> 01:25:51.279
Can I come with you?

01:25:54.280 --> 01:25:55.474
No.

01:25:59.600 --> 01:26:01.158
Thank you.

01:26:06.440 --> 01:26:07.839
<i>Are those handcuffs?</i>

01:26:08.760 --> 01:26:10.751
I mean, obviously they're handcuffs.

01:26:10.920 --> 01:26:13.070
You're Lucas, right?
The state trooper?

01:26:14.800 --> 01:26:16.279
Do you mind?

01:26:23.280 --> 01:26:24.838
<i>All right, thank you.</i>

01:26:26.120 --> 01:26:28.714
Too much to ask for you
to punch me in the face?

01:26:30.440 --> 01:26:33.637
You know, forget it. Never mind.
Thank you.

01:26:41.120 --> 01:26:42.439
<b><font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE STARTING)</font></b>

01:27:24.640 --> 01:27:26.358
Needs to be tighter.

01:27:33.040 --> 01:27:34.553
Lift your arms up.

01:27:40.800 --> 01:27:42.119
How's that feel?

01:27:42.280 --> 01:27:43.349
Good.

01:27:45.840 --> 01:27:47.671
- Dad?
- Yeah?

01:27:50.560 --> 01:27:52.198
Are you scared?

01:27:58.040 --> 01:27:59.189
Yes.

01:28:02.880 --> 01:28:04.871
You don't have to worry about me.

01:28:07.040 --> 01:28:09.110
I like worrying about you.

01:28:12.120 --> 01:28:14.111
You don't have to anymore.

01:28:20.120 --> 01:28:22.680
I'll always worry about you, Alton.

01:28:23.720 --> 01:28:25.358
